<center>
<h4 style="padding-right: 30px;padding-bottom: 50px; padding-left: 80px;">The internet is a job seeker’s most crucial tool to success today. From connecting with potential employers online to<br> researching job hunting best practices, it’s a goldmine of opportunity.<br>
  With so much information on what’s right and wrong and hot or <br>not in the job seeking world, how do you filter out the the high quality content from the junk? <br>There are countless blogs on how to write the perfect resume and how to follow up after an interview and it’s hard to tell who really knows what they’re talking about.
<br>We’ve weeded through hundreds of job hunting blogs to bring you our 5 favorites,<br> with quality content and awesome advice, add these to your RSS feed today!

</h4>
</center>
</div>

<div class = "col-sm-4" style="padding-top: 50px;padding-right: 30px;padding-bottom: 50px; padding-left: 80px;" >
<h3><b>CAREEREALISM</b></h3><br><h5>With over 78,000 daily subscribers, Careerealism has quickly become one of the top resources for job seekers. New articles are posted on a daily basis and cover almost everything you would ever want to know about as a jobseeker. Topics range from general job search advice to detailed LinkedIn tips and best practices, this is a resource you don’t want to miss!</h5>
</div>
<div class = "col-sm-4" style="padding-top: 50px;padding-right: 30px;padding-bottom: 50px; padding-left: 80px;" >

<h3><b>MASHABLE JOBS</b></h3><br><h5>One of the most well known websites in our industry today, Mashable,  has a jobs section chock-full of information applicable to job seekers. They report on the latest social media trends for job seekers and discuss new ways to expand your network . This is the place to be for up to date information on the job seeking world.</h5>
</div>
<div class = "col-sm-4" style="padding-top: 50px;padding-right: 30px;padding-bottom: 50px; padding-left: 80px;" >
<h3><b>CAREERBUILDER WORK BUZZ</b></h3><br><h5>Lots of job seekers peruse CareerBuilder for jobs but did you know they have an awesome blog as well? With categories such as ‘find the job’ and ‘get the job’ you can rely on these experts for consistent content. Each week you can find new articles on a variety of subjects as well as a searchable jobs section.</h5> 
</div>
<div class="col-sm-4" style="padding-top: 50px;padding-right: 30px;padding-bottom: 50px; padding-left: 80px;">
<h3><b>SIMPLYHIRED BLOG</b></h3><br><h5>While it’s not a flashy site, SimplyHired (similar to CareerBuilder) provides some excellent job seeking gems you’ll want to know about. Averaging about a post a day, this is a great resource for more in-depth articles and topics.</h5>
</div>
<div class="col-sm-4" style="padding-top: 50px;padding-right: 30px;padding-bottom: 50px; padding-left: 80px;">
<h3><b>BRAZEN LIFE</b></h3><br><h5>Whether you’re looking to optimize your current position or on the job hunt, Brazen is an essential resource. From entry-level advice to start-up advice, you can find what you’re looking for. Most articles usually have interesting comment sections where you can learn from job seekers just like yourself.</h5>
</div>
<center><h5>One of your most valuable resources as a job seeker is the internet and online communities with awesome advice for people like you. Don’t be afraid to get involved and do your research! What are your favorite job hunt blogs?
